wikipedia_page.main: Baron Luitbert Alexander George Lionel Alphons von Pawel-Rammingen,  (German: Luitbert Alexander Georg Lionel Alfons Freiherr von Pawel-Rammingen; 27 July 1843 – 20 November 1932) was a German-born nobleman who became a naturalised British subject in 1880 when he married Princess Frederica of Hanover.
